The paper discusses similarity search in large and multidimensional data spaces, which is a common problem in database research (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of metric geometry concepts and techniques suggests that the paper could also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper also mentions probability metric spaces, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
